history.content:
Hey everyone!

EE/CS Community Week is an effort by several EECS-related organizations to foster a community within an environment where it has become too easy to feel anonymous and unsupported. We all have experienced not getting into the majors, the jobs, or the clubs that we work so hard for. This week is an opportunity for our community to come together to foster a more welcoming and inclusive environment!

If you are interested, we have several different events LIVE on our Facebook Page https://www.facebook.com/eecscommunityweek/ categorized into academic-related events and wellness events! Please consider going to one or more events to support the cause!

We also have one-on-one mentorship session planned for the week! These sessions are central to EE/CS Community Week. If you are interested in being a mentor: https://forms.gle/wVJMqhv7SXu4rCJs6. Mentee sign-ups will be released in the next several days, but if you are interested in becoming a mentee please fill out this interest survey! https://forms.gle/ZK5WFLbUbieKZN3s5

Thank you all so much for your support this semester and I cannot wait to see all of you during EE/CS Community Week!
